The article provides background information on President Obama's trip to Buffalo, New York. He is scheduled to visit Industrial Support Inc, tour their manufacturing facilities, and deliver remarks on the economy. The audience will mainly consist of workers and guests of Industrial Support Inc, as well as local small businesses, elected officials, and community leaders. The article also provides information about the individuals leading the tour, including David Sullivan, the founder and president of Industrial Support Inc, and Anthony Sabuda and Max Branham, vice presidents of the company. Industrial Support Inc specializes in contract manufacturing services and has experienced significant growth since its founding in 1995. They have received recognition for their success and hope to further expand their business with the help of an SBA Recovery Act loan.